<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP TENNIS; PENINSULA GIRLS WIN TITLE AGAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG SANDOVAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Top-seeded Palos Verdes Peninsula captured its fourth consecutive Southern 
Section Division I girls' team tennis title by defeating Corona del Mar, 17-1, 
Tuesday morning at the Claremont Club. 
</P>
<P>
 Amanda Augustus, the No. 1 singles player for Peninsula, won her matches, 6-2, 
6-1, 6-0. 
</P>
<P>
 With the victory, Peninsula (24-0) improved its four-year winning streak to 96 
matches. 
</P>
<P>
 In other finals: 
</P>
<P>
 -- Laguna Beach won a third consecutive title by defeating Los Alamitos, 12-6, 
in Division II. 
</P>
<P>
 -- Placentia El Dorado was unable to win a fifth point in the doubles play and 
lost to Pasadena Poly, 9-9 (79-76 in games) in Division III. 
</P>
<P>
 -- Palm Desert was led by No. 1 singles player Staci Smith in its 11-7 victory 
over Brentwood in Division IV. GREG SANDOVAL 
</P>
</TEXT>
