<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISHING REPORT: ANAHEIM ANGLER HAULS IN 29-POUND STURGEON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It's no secret that trout can't resist Power Bait, but this is ridiculous. 
</P>
<P>
 Armando Burqueno of Anaheim put a glob of the rainbow-colored goop on his hook 
and hauled in a prehistoric-looking sturgeon. 
</P>
<P>
 Sturgeon are rarely caught at Irvine Lake, and Burqueno must have thought he 
hooked into a monster trout. The fish pulled him around for 1 hour 45 minutes 
before coming to the surface. It was netted and brought to the scale alive, 
weighed in at 29 pounds, then released. 
</P>
</TEXT>
