<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRO FOOTBALL DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE NFL; ALBERTS RETURNS EARLY FOR COLTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Linebacker Trev Alberts expects to make his debut for the Indianapolis Colts 
on Sunday. Alberts, a first-round draft pick, dislocated his right elbow in the 
Colts' opening exhibition game, and was expected to sit out the entire season. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Dallas Cowboys signed Tommy Hodson as a backup quarterback to Jason 
Garrett. He beat out fellow veteran free agent Mike Pagel. . . . The Houston 
Oilers declined Webster Slaughter's request for a release. The receiver is 
unhappy about being benched after the team scrapped the run-and-shoot for a two 
wide receiver offense. . . . New York Giant Coach Dan Reeves said Dave Brown 
will start at quarterback Sunday at Washington. . . . The Green Bay Packers 
said they will leave first-round draft pick Aaron Taylor, sidelined all season 
because of a knee injury, on the physically unable to perform list for the rest 
of the season. 
</P>
