<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: GARDENA; 2 CONVICTED OF 
MURDERING MAN AT HIS FRONT DOOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two Carson gang members face 30 years to life in prison for gunning down a 
Gardena man when he answered his doorbell Nov. 16, 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 A Torrance Superior Court jury convicted Jeremiah Angel DeGuzman, 20, and John 
Paul Madrona, 19, of murder after deliberating for about four hours Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 The two men shot Tracy Takahashi, 30, in a case of mistaken identity. DeGuzman 
and Madrona thought Takahashi was a rival gang member when he opened the front 
door of his apartment on South Dalton Avenue about 12:30 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Deputy Dist. Atty. Gregory D. Jennings said he will seek the maximum prison 
sentence for both men. Sentencing is set for Dec. 9. 
</P>
<P>
 The three-week trial was held before Judge John P. Shook. 
</P>
<P>
 Attorneys for the defendants could not be reached for comment. 
</P>
