<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: MISCELLANY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kansas State quarterback Chad May, a former starter at Cal State Fullerton, 
was selected first-team All-Big Eight for the second consecutive season, the 
school announced. 
</P>
<P>
 May led Kansas State to an 8-2 record and an Aloha Bowl berth Dec. 25. He 
completed 59% of his passes for 2,445 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Kim Hamrock of Huntington Beach advanced to the final of the women's division 
of the U.S. Amateur Surfing Championships Tuesday in Sebastian Inlet, Fla. 
</P>
<P>
 Jason Bean of Huntington Beach and Philip Harnsberger of Santa Barbara tied 
for fifth in the senior bodyboard division. 
</P>
