<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLISSON COMMITS TO WILLIAM & MARY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Christy Collisson, a three-year starting setter for the Laguna Beach girls' 
volleyball team, orally committed to William & Mary, her coach said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Pacific Coast League coaches selected Collisson, 17, all-league the last two 
seasons. Collisson, 5 feet 9, also was an All-Southern Section Division I pick 
as a junior. 
</P>
<P>
 Artist Coach Mike Soylular said Collisson will study international relations 
at the Williamsburg, Va., school. 
</P>
