<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' VOLLEYBALL STATE PLAYOFF ROUNDUP; CALVARY CHAPEL SERVES UP VICTORY OVER 
CLAIREMONT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAN ARRITT, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Julee Elliott had eight of Calvary Chapel's 18 aces as the top-seeded Eagles 
easily swept San Diego Clairemont, 15-4, 15-1, 15-3, in the first round of the 
girls' volleyball Southern California Regionals Tuesday at Calvary Chapel. 
</P>
<P>
 The Eagles never trailed in the match, which took only 50 minutes. 
</P>
<P>
 It was a repeat of last year's first-round matchup, which Calvary Chapel also 
swept en route to the Division IV State final, which the Eagles lost in four 
games to San Jose Archbishop Mitty. 
</P>
<P>
 Calvary Chapel (18-4) will play host to Holtville a winner in four games over 
Sierra Madre Maranatha, in the second round Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Clairemont (16-5) was the runner-up in the San Diego Section Division IV 
playoffs, but was clearly not the caliber of team Calvary Chapel faced in the 
Southern Section, which the Eagles won Saturday against Santa Ynez. 
</P>
<P>
 "We have to play every game like it's important," Calvary Chapel Coach Jim 
Downey said. "We have to keep going out there and try to improve." 
</P>
<P>
 The Eagles took a 6-2 lead in the opening minutes as Whitney Hoover started 
the game with two aces and Sara Roberts and Jenny Roberts had two kills. 
</P>
<P>
 Kelly Eikermann's kill then made it 14-4 and Lynn Lovingier finished the game 
with another ace for the Eagles. 
</P>
<P>
 The Eagles continued to serve tough in Game 2, getting eight aces. 
</P>
<P>
 Elliott rotated in the game and aced five of the last seven points for Calvary 
Chapel.  
</P>
<P>
 Clairemont seemed to adjust to the serves early in the third game, but Elliott 
again rotated in and had three aces for a 15-3 victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Jenny Roberts led the Eagles with seven kills and Courtney Owens added four. 
</P>
<P>
 In a Division V match: 
</P>
<P>
 La Jolla Bishop's 3, St. Margaret's 0 -- The Tartans lost, 15-6, 15-4, 15-4, 
and end with an 11-6 record. 
</P>
</TEXT>
