<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL 1994-1995: ORANGE LEAGUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 MAGNOLIA 03,17,09,08 1993-94 RECORDS OVERALL LEAGUE 18-9 7-3 COACH: Doug Romeo 
</P>
<P>
 RECORD AT SCHOOL: 53-62 04,20,05,06,04 RETURNING STARTERS YR. HGT. P Andrea 
Picchi Jr. 5-11 F 04,17,05,06,04 TOP RETURNERS YR. HGT. P Jaclyn Chairez Sr. 
5-6 F Mary Tuazon Sr. 5-4 G Michelle Tuazon Sr. 5-2 G 04,19,05,06,04 TOP 
NEWCOMERS YR. HGT. P Sophia Garcia Sr. 5-6 F Pomaao Jackson Jr. 5-9 C Sheree 
McLellan Jr. 5-7 F Amber Pickett Jr. 5-5 G Stacy Tewell So. 5-11 C Michelle 
Williams So. 5-4 G OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 Romeo, last year's Orange League coach of the year, returns only one starter 
from last year's team that advanced to the Southern Section III-AA 
quarterfinals. Losing all-leaguers Barbara Mathews and Whitney Torregano leaves 
a huge hole on defense and in experience. Romeo says Magnolia will have to 
overachieve in order to match the accomplishments of last year's squad. Picchi, 
the lone returning starter, is back for her fourth year in the starting lineup. 
She will be joined by Mary and Michelle Tuazon and Chairez, who will help out 
with ballhandling. Despite Picchi (5-11) and Tewell (5-11), the Sentinels lack 
physical size. Pickett was last year's junior varsity MVP and Williams should 
back up Mary Tuazon at point guard. Romeo says in order for this team to be 
successful, the newcomers will have to adjust to the varsity level in a hurry. 
If they avoid injuries, the Sentinels should still be in contention for a 
return trip to the playoffs. SCHEDULE 
</P>
