<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL 1994-1995: ORANGE LEAGUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 SAVANNA 03,17,09,08 1993-94 RECORDS OVERALL LEAGUE 4-17 1-9 COACH: Greg 
Higashi 
</P>
<P>
 RECORD AT SCHOOL: 4-17 04,20,05,06,04 RETURNING STARTERS YR. HGT. P Amy 
Klingelsmith Sr. 5-10 F Shauna Miller Sr. 5-7 G 04,21,05,06,05 TOP RETURNERS 
YR. HGT. P Diana Hernandez Sr. 5-7 G/F Shannon Pendergraft So. 5-7 G Michele 
Stevens Sr. 6-1 C Mina Van Pham Sr. 5-2 G 04,17,05,06,05 TOP NEWCOMERS YR. HGT. 
P Carmela Antonio Sr. 5-2 G Marisa Barba So. 5-4 G Alicia Olson Jr. 5-6 G/F 
April Olson Jr. 5-6 G/F OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 For the second consecutive season, Higashi returns two starters. This season, 
unfortunately, he doesn't have the luxury of building from a 12-12 team that 
reached the playoffs. The Rebels managed only one league victory last season, 
but should be improved this season. Klingelsmith and Miller are back for their 
senior years. Klingelsmith averaged nine points last season and earned 
all-league honorable mention honors. She will be joined by Stevens and 
Hernandez in the post. Stevens who was a part-time starter last season, will 
earn the starting job at center by the time the season starts. Pendergraft is 
also expected to help fill the holes left by graduation. The abundance of 
seniors should offset the team's lack of height, but the Rebels will have a 
tough time hanging with Valencia, Western and Magnolia for the league's third 
playoff berth. With five girls on the volleyball team and two playing tennis, 
Higashi is glad to finally have a full team at practice. Higashi said this 
year's squad is deeper than a year ago's. SCHEDULE 
</P>
