<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL 1994-1995: ORANGE LEAGUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 ANAHEIM 03,17,09,08 1993-94 RECORDS OVERALL LEAGUE 6-13 1-9 COACH: Lori Giroux 
</P>
<P>
 RECORD AT SCHOOL: 6-32 04,20,05,06,04 RETURNING STARTERS YR. HGT. P Charisse 
Correa Sr. 5-7 F Stephanie Durrett Jr. 5-9 C Debbie Tu'ua Sr. 5-6 G 
04,18,05,06,04 TOP RETURNERS YR. HGT. P Kellie Fernandez Sr. 5-8 F Hiroko 
Todoroki Sr. 5-2 G Amber Woodberry Sr. 5-6 F 04,21,05,06,04 TOP NEWCOMERS YR. 
HGT. P Angelica Hernandez Sr. 5-4 F Jo-Ann Koo Sr. 5-2 G Mahogany McClelland 
Sr. 5-3 G OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 The Colonists may be the most oldest team in the league, but unfortunately for 
Giroux, that doesn't always translate into victories. Giroux enters her third 
season with five seniors and one junior returning from last year's last-place 
team. She says the experience should help boost confidence, considering the 
Colonists won six games last season after going winless two seasons ago. Tu'ua 
will be one of the team leaders, off a junior season that saw her average eight 
points and win all-league honorable mention honors. Durrett will also be looked 
to for scoring, after averaging three points last season, as well as Todoroki. 
Replacing the point production from four-year starter Maricela Roque at forward 
will be one of Giroux's biggest challenges. The Colonists add seniors Koo and 
McClelland to help with backcourt duties, but they lack size and depth in the 
post. The lack of size and scoring, along with some stiff league competition, 
might be too much to overcome for the Colonists to reach the playoffs. SCHEDULE 
</P>
<P>
 November 28 at Industry Workman; 30 at Irvine tournament. 
</P>
