<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL 1994-1995: ORANGE LEAGUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 WESTERN 03,17,09,08 1993-94 RECORDS OVERALL LEAGUE 11-14 5-5 COACH: Michael 
Mercer 
</P>
<P>
 RECORD AT SCHOOL: 0-0 04,22,05,06,05 RETURNING STARTERS YR. HGT. P Jennifer 
Christensen Sr. 5-4 G Nancy Herrera Jr. 5-6 G/F Adrienne Ratajczak So. 5-8 G/F 
04,17,05,06,04 TOP RETURNERS YR. HGT. P Shannon Siefken Sr. 5-11 C 
04,18,05,06,05 TOP NEWCOMERS YR. HGT. P Jessica Castillo So. 6-0 C Brandy 
Mercer Fr. 5-7 G/F Pearl Mercer Sr. 5-11 C/F Myiesha Ray Sr. 5-6 G OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 Mercer inherits three starters from last year's fourth-place team. First-team 
all-league selection Jennifer Christensen is back at guard for her senior year. 
She will be relied upon to not only run the offense, but also contribute points 
on the board. Herrera and Brandy Mercer are also expected to help with the 
scoring. Coach Mercer says guard Mercer is one of the best freshmen in the 
county, and that's not because she's his daughter. Sister Pearl, a transfer 
from Loara, will add experience, along with fellow senior Siefken. Inexperience 
is Mercer's biggest concern, and rightfully so. Most of the newcomers have 
never played varsity ball before. Team speed could help alleviate the lack of 
experience. Ray, a transfer from Troy, will add to the depth in the backcourt. 
Mercer says a playoff berth would be nice, but it's not a priority. Another 
.500 record is the team's first priority. Expect the Sentinels to battle with 
Savanna and Western for a playoff berth. SCHEDULE 
</P>
<P>
 November 29 at Trabuco Hills; 30 at Fullerton tournament. 
</P>
