GIRLS' BASKETBALL 1994-1995: ORANGE LEAGUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 VALENCIA 03,17,09,08 1993-94 RECORDS OVERALL LEAGUE 13-10 6-4 COACH: James 
Corbitt 
</P>
<P>
 RECORD AT SCHOOL: 0-0 04,20,05,06,05 RETURNING STARTERS YR. HGT. P LaQuinta 
Alexander Sr. 6-0 C/F Cindi Judd Sr. 5-4 G Tina Katz Sr. 5-5 G Michelle Prager 
Jr. 5-9 F Jaime Snavely Sr. 5-10 G/F 04,17,05,06,05 TOP RETURNERS YR. HGT. P 
Shelly Gamba Jr. 5-7 G/F Melissa Nevares Jr. 5-6 G 04,16,05,06,04 TOP NEWCOMERS 
YR. HGT. P Belinda Lee Jr. 5-6 G Heather Hoppe Fr. 5-6 G Roxanna Stumph So. 6-1 
C OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 Corbitt has plenty of high hopes entering his first season at Valencia. He 
inherits five starters from a third-place team that advanced to the second 
round of the Southern Section II-A playoffs. This group looks to be better than 
last year's and is a unanimous pick by the rest of the league to finish second. 
However, Corbitt says the starting positions are not etched in stone. Alexander 
and Judd were all-league selections last season and join Snavely and Katz as 
returning seniors. Alexander averaged 11.8 points and Judd averaged 7.5. Lee 
could break into the starting lineup, as could Stumph and Gamba; Nevares and 
Hoppe are expected to play a lot. Corbitt says the emphasis this season will be 
on a strong defense and outside shooting. A deep bench, good inside game and 
strong underclassmen make the Tigers even stronger. Since he's unfamiliar with 
the league, Corbitt is content to call his team the dark horse, but believes it 
will able to contend with any team in the county. SCHEDULE 
</P>
