<P>
 The 12-time defending league champions enter the season with a new coach for 
the third consecutive season. Every time the Ladycats lose a handful of 
seniors, a letdown is expected. And every time a letdown is expected, the 
Ladycats respond. The team enters the season riding a 54-game winning streak, 
one short of the team record set from 1989-91. Another undefeated season would 
break the Southern Section record of 84 in a row by Riverside Poly from 
1978-82. Sink is no stranger to winning. He won 11 league and two state titles 
in 14 years at Lathrop High in Fairbanks, Alaska. Moulin, who averaged nine 
points last season, earned all-league and all-CIF honors. Miller, also an 
all-league and all-CIF selection, averaged 11 points. Helping fill the void 
left by Nicole Erickson, Colleen Hudson and Co. is Saari, who will run the 
offense, Metz and Zachry. Bradley averaged 18.5 points as a freshman on the 
junior varsity. Another league title should be a lock. A fifth state title, 
maybe not. SCHEDULE 
