<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; HARVARD ADVANCES IN VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Harvard-Westlake High defeated La Jolla, 15-6, 15-4, 15-5, in the first round 
of the State Division III girls' volleyball tournament Tuesday night at La 
Jolla High. 
</P>
<P>
 The Wolverines (16-5) avenged a four-game setback to La Jolla in the first 
round of last season's State tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Senior Amanda Selby, who will play at UCLA next season, had 13 kills as 
Harvard-Westlake disposed of the Vikings (27-8) in 50 minutes. 
</P>
<P>
 Teammate Lesley Coben added eight kills, while Carolyn Miller contributed four 
aces. 
</P>
<P>
 Harvard-Westlake, which entered the Southern Section playoffs unseeded, will 
meet Bakersfield Centennial on Saturday at a site to be determined. 
</P>
<P>
 The victory was the eighth in nine matches for Mission League champion 
Harvard-Westlake, which lost in the Southern Section semifinals to Long Beach 
Millikan. 
</P>
<P>
 Bakersfield Stockdale d. Agoura, 15-4, 16-14, 15-10 -- The Marmonte League 
champion Chargers (15-4) fell in the first round of the Division II state 
playoffs in Bakersfield. 
</P>
<P>
 Casie Hyatt had 16 kills for second-seeded Stockdale and Jill Levey added 29 
assists. 
</P>
<P>
 Auberry Sierra d. L.A. Baptist, 15-13, 15-8, 16-14 -- The Knights (19-2) were 
eliminated in the first round of the State Division IV playoffs at Tollhouse. 
</P>
<P>
 Jamie Rempel had 12 blocks, and Roxanne Waggle had eight kills to lead Sierra 
(22-7), while Audrey Nesser was 19-of-19 serving, including three aces. WOMEN'S 
VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Mt. San Antonio d. Moorpark, 19-17, 8-15, 8-15, 15-11, 15-11 -- Dawn Smith had 
24 kills, but the Raiders (13-6) fell to the Mounties in the first round of the 
state junior college volleyball playoffs in Walnut. 
</P>
<P>
 Teammate Tami Vaillancourt added 19 kills for Moorpark, while Gretchen 
Gulbranson had 68 assists. WOMEN'S BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Biola 78, The Master's 69 -- Kim De Vries scored 21 points, Jodi Ageuda added 
19 and Deborah Prociw had 16, but the Mustangs (1-3) lost at La Mirada. Ivana 
Kvacic scored 22 points for Biola (1-2). Lynell Johnson scored 12 points, and 
Courtney Dunham, Yvette Williams and Susan Flaming each had 11 for Biola. 
</P>
<P>
 Valley 64, Desert 58 -- Valley's Erika Kusek came off the bench to score 15 
points -- including three three-point baskets -- and had seven rebounds in a 
nonconference game in Van Nuys. Maggie Hause added 14 points -- including four 
three-pointers -- for the Monarchs (4-0).  
</P>
<P>
 Nancy Pinzon scored 16 points for Desert (0-3). BOYS' SOCCER 
</P>
<P>
 Chatsworth 3, Grant 0 -- Michael Price, Yobani Cruz and Guy Klein scored for 
the Chancellors (1-0-1) in the second round of the Reseda tournament. Grant is 
0-1-1. 
</P>
