</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: TWO SWIMMERS SIGN WITH CS NORTHRIDGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Cal State Northridge women's swim team announced the signing of two new 
recruits Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Kim Piorto, from Mesa, Ariz., and Julie White from Milwaukee, Wis., will swim 
freestyle for the Matadors next season.Piorto has a 3.9 grade-point average, 
and White, who also swims in backstroke events, has a 3.8 GPA. College Football 
</P>
<P>
 Valley College (9-1) is ranked ninth and Moorpark (8-2) is 10th in the final 
state junior college football poll. City College of San Francisco (10-0) is 
ranked No. 1. Basketball 
</P>
<P>
 Chaminade High has added an impact player to its girls' basketball program. 
</P>
<P>
 Sheila Shalati, a transfer from the state of Washington, enrolled at the 
school four weeks ago and already has earned a starting position at point 
guard. 
</P>
<P>
 "She's really a great addition for us," Coach Lisa Magorien said of the 
5-foot-1 Shalati. "She's added a whole new level to the program." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Burbank High will hold its alumni game tonight at 7. All former players are 
invited. For information, contact Jeff Davis at 818-558-4700 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Tarzana Recreation Center is accepting registration for its youth basketball 
leagues. There are openings in all age levels. Information: 818-343-5946 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Three former high school all-Americans will participate in Crescenta Valley 
High's annual alumni contest tonight at 8. 
</P>
<P>
 Greg Goorjian, Brad Holland, and Harvey Mason will lead a team of former 
Falcon standouts against coach John Goffredo's current squad. Soccer  
</P>
<P>
 Sarah Morgan, a freshman at Notre Dame High, has been selected to the 
California's south team of the girls' under 15 soccer Olympic development club. 
Morgan is 14. 
</P>
