<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOSNIAN FOUND GUILTY OF WAR CRIMES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Bosnian who fled to Denmark as a refugee was found guilty Tuesday of 
torturing fellow Muslims to death in a POW camp in his homeland and given eight 
years in prison. 
</P>
<P>
 The Copenhagen regional court's verdict was the first in a series of war 
crimes trials being held outside the former Yugoslav federation. 
</P>
<P>
 The court found Refic Saric, 31, guilty on 14 counts of gross violence, two 
leading to the deaths of the victims. Saric claimed he was a victim of mistaken 
identity. He was declared mentally ill after arriving in Denmark with his wife 
and two children and will be given psychiatric care until he is well enough to 
serve time in jail. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
