<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: SADDLEBACK / SOUTH BEACH; LAGUNA NIGUEL; OLYMPIC GOLD 
MEDAL HOLDER TO LEAD PARADE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LYNN FRANEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city's fifth annual Holiday Parade is taking shape, with gymnast and 
Olympic gold medalist Peter Vidmar agreeing to be grand marshal and 15 Southern 
California marching bands signing on to participate. 
</P>
<P>
 On Dec. 10, Vidmar will lead a two-hour parade that will include the United 
States Marine Corps Mounted Color Guard, equestrian units, drill teams, and 
community youth and service clubs along Crown Valley Parkway beginning at 10 
a.m. The parade will start at Nueva Vista Road and end at Niguel Road. 
</P>
<P>
 Vidmar, a Foothill Ranch resident, was captain of the United States men's 
gymnastics team that won its first-ever gold medal during the 1984 Olympic 
Games in Los Angeles. He is the highest scoring U.S. gymnast in Olympic history 
and is a member of the Governor's Council on Physical Fitness and Sport for the 
state of California. 
</P>
<P>
 The parade will begin a two-day Holiday Festival, set to run from 10 a.m. to 5 
p.m. Dec. 10 and 11 at Crown Valley Community Park. The free festival will 
offer kiddie rides and puppet shows, photos with Santa Claus, international 
foods, arts and crafts, and live music. LYNN FRANEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
