<P>
 GARDEN GROVE / Workers Bank on Doggone Good Cause 
</P>
<P>
 Who: Farmers & Merchants Bank employees 
</P>
<P>
 Contribution: Bank employees washed cars, sold baked goods and hosted a garage 
sale to raise $1,000 for the Garden Grove Police Department's Canine Fund. The 
money will be used to train police dogs in narcotics detection, according to 
Police Chief Stanley L. Knee. "This caught us completely by surprise," he said. 
"But this kind of support from members of our business community is truly 
appreciated." The bank employees decided to raise the money after a 
presentation on bank safety and crime prevention by Officers Todd Langus and 
Mike Scalise, and their canine partners, Thunder and Nero. Donations may be 
sent to the Police Canine Fund, City of Garden Grove, P.O. Box 3070, Garden 
Grove, CA 92642. SANTA ANA / Bar Bests Its '93 Largess by a Ton 
</P>
<P>
 Who: Orange County Bar Assn. 
</P>
<P>
 Contribution: Donated more than four tons of food during the association's 
second annual food drive to help the hungry. The collection bettered 1993 
donations by a ton. The collected food was donated to the Food Distribution 
Center of Orange County, established in 1983 as a private, nonprofit food bank. 
The Orange County office of the law firm O'Melveny & Myers led the drive, 
collecting 2,659 pounds. NEWPORT BEACH / $9,000 Raised for Needy Children 
</P>
<P>
 Who: Assistance League of Newport-Mesa 
</P>
<P>
 Contribution: Raised $9,000 to benefit school programs for needy children at 
its annual boat rally in late September. The competing teams had to decorate 
their boats and wear movie-themed costumes while following clues from the 
Balboa Bay Club to stops including the homes of Shirley Temple and Joseph 
Wambaugh. Newport Beach resident Bill Lanjhar, in his boat, "Ohm Work," was the 
rally's overall winner. The best costume award went to the Wayt family for 
"Aladdin," while Lester Hale's "M.A.S.H." entry took the best-decorated prize. 
The league has 700 members in the area who help children of low-income families 
with school clothes, vaccinations and health examinations and dental care 
clinics. IRVINE / Volunteer Is Gifted Fund-Raiser 
</P>
<P>
 Who: Irene Ziebarth 
</P>
<P>
 Contribution: Recently named one of several volunteers of the year by Cal 
State Fullerton. She is a five-year member of the President's Associates and 
has raised $25,000 for the organization. She has also hosted events, recruited 
members and worked to renew memberships for the campus group. She is also a 
four-year member of the campus Executive Committee. 
</P>
