<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: CENTRAL; SANTA ANA; BURGLARY SUSPECT JAILED AFTER SCUFFLE 
IN MALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By THAO HUA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A parolee accused of burglarizing a department store, then striking a Santa 
Ana police officer on the head with the bag of stolen items was in jail 
Tuesday, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Herman Mackey Jr., 42, of Fullerton was arrested Monday afternoon, hours after 
scuffling with Santa Ana Officer Steve Chavez at MainPlace/Santa Ana, where the 
suspect tried to steal $469 worth of leather purses, wallets and eyeglass 
cases, said Santa Ana Officer Jack Wipple. 
</P>
<P>
 "The officer tried to stop him," Wipple said, "but (Mackey) broke free and ran 
away." 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton police spotted Mackey more than four hours later in front of a motel 
in the 2600 block of West Orangethorpe Avenue, where he was arrested on 
suspicion of burglary, criminal conspiracy, possession of narcotics and assault 
on a police officer. All of the stolen items were retrieved. He is being held 
without bail at Orange County Jail. 
</P>
<P>
 Mackey has been on parole since Jan. 21, after serving more than three years 
at Pelican Bay State Prison in Crescent City, authorities said. Police and 
parole officers would not release information on his convictions, saying it is 
against department policy. 
</P>
<P>
 Two men seen leaving the scene of the assault after the scuffle also were 
arrested on suspicion of criminal conspiracy, Wipple said. Ruben Vidaurreta, 
34, of Santa Ana and David Wilson Wheeler, 39, of Fullerton remain in jail in 
lieu of $10,000 bail. Vidaurreta was taken to the Santa Ana Detention Center 
and Wheeler to Orange County Jail. THAO HUA 
</P>
</TEXT>
