<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY ALMANAC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chapman University might not be Orange County's largest or most famous 
institution of higher learning. But it is one of the oldest. 
</P>
<P>
 In fact, five buildings on the campus are listed on the National Register of 
Historic Places. 
</P>
<P>
 The neoclassical buildings, constructed between 1904 and 1928, are considered 
to be one of the largest concentrations of historic buildings in the county, 
according to college officials. 
</P>
<P>
 The exteriors of all five buildings -- Wilkinson Hall, Memorial Hall, Smith 
Hall, Reeves Hall and Founders Hall -- are mostly unchanged from their original 
appearance. Today 
</P>
<P>
 Some musicians plan to rock the house at a Yorba Linda church tonight. 
</P>
<P>
 The Salvation Army Band, Choir and Timbrel Corps will perform a varied musical 
program at 7:30. 
</P>
<P>
 The free concert will be in the sanctuary of Yorba Linda United Methodist 
Church. 
</P>
<P>
 The church is located at 19002 Yorba Linda Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (714) 777-2885. 
</P>
</TEXT>
