COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: NEWPORT / COSTA MESA / IRVINE; NEWPORT BEACH; 
RENT-A-SANTA PROGRAM ACCEPTING RESERVATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Newport Beach is accepting reservations for its Rent-a-Santa program. 
</P>
<P>
 For a minimum charge of $30 per half-hour, residents and businesses can get a 
visit from Santa at holiday parties anytime from 10 a.m. to 10 p.m. Dec. 1 
through Dec. 23.Santa visits will include candy canes for each guest. 
</P>
<P>
 Paid reservations must be made at least 24 hours in advance. Santa has a busy 
schedule, so visits are arranged on a first-come, first-served basis. 
</P>
<P>
 Visits are available in Corona del Mar, Newport Beach and parts of Costa Mesa. 
Last year, Santa visited 93 parties in the area. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call Maria Oliver at (714) 644-3154. 
</P>
