COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: NEWPORT / COSTA MESA / IRVINE; NEWPORT BEACH; HUMAN 
OPTIONS PLANS HOLIDAY BENEFIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Human Options, an organization that provides temporary housing to battered 
women and children, is planning a Champagne High Tea and auction benefit Dec. 
1. 
</P>
<P>
 The eighth annual Starry, Starry Night benefit is themed "A Victorian Holiday" 
and will include trips, restaurant dinners, packaged holiday baskets, theater 
tickets and more. 
</P>
<P>
 The tea will be from 2:30 to 5:30 p.m. at Gustav Anders in South Coast Plaza 
Village. Tickets are $45 each and available by calling Human Options, at (714) 
497-5620. 
</P>
<P>
 Human Options provides housing, counseling and community education to help end 
domestic violence. The organization recently broke ground for an emergency 
shelter in Irvine. 
