<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: NEWPORT / COSTA MESA / IRVINE; NEWPORT BEACH; LIBRARY 
WANTS ADVICE FROM YOUNG ADULTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The public library is seeking junior and senior high school students to serve 
on its Young Adult Advisory Council. 
</P>
<P>
 Participants serve two-year terms that include one- to two-hour monthly 
meetings at the Newport Beach Central Library, 1000 Avocado Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 Applicants must be between the ages of 12 and 18 and live in Newport Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 The task requires a strong interest in helping the public library serve young 
people. The council members will review materials and services available to 
their age group and recommend changes and set goals. 
</P>
<P>
 Applications are available at the children's desks of all Newport Beach 
library branches and at public school libraries in the city. The application 
deadline is today. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call Youth Services Manager Judy Kelley at (714) 
717-3807. 
</P>
