<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: NEWPORT / COSTA MESA / IRVINE; NEWPORT BEACH; CITY STILL 
HAS TICKETS FOR ROSE PARADE TRIP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city has a limited number of tickets remaining for its annual bus 
excursion to the Tournament of Roses Parade in Pasadena. 
</P>
<P>
 The $65 ticket price includes deluxe charter bus transportation, grandstand 
seating and a boxed lunch. Buses will depart from Mariners Park, 2005 Dover 
Drive, at 6:30 a.m. and return about 2 p.m. Jan. 2. The theme for this year's 
parade is "Sports -- Quest for Excellence." 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets are available by phone, mail or in person at the Community Services 
Department, Newport Beach City Hall, 3300 Newport Blvd. For credit card orders, 
call (714) 644-3151. 
</P>
