<P>
WOMAN, DOG DIE IN LAGUNA HOUSE FIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An unidentified woman and a dog were killed Tuesday in a fire that engulfed a 
house in the 400 block of Blumont Street, according to fire officials. 
</P>
<P>
 About 20 to 25 firefighters from Laguna Beach and the Orange County Fire 
Department responded about 7 p.m. after a neighbor alerted them, according to 
Battalion Chief Joe McClure. 
</P>
<P>
 By the time firefighters arrived, the house, built in the 1930s, was engulfed 
in flames. It took just over an hour to control the fire, McClure said.  
</P>
<P>
 The woman's body was found in the kitchen-living room area. Neighbors said the 
victim was retired and lived alone with her dog. 
</P>
<P>
 There were no winds at the time of the fire, McClure said, and nearby 
structures that were threatened were protected from the fire. 
</P>
