<TEXT>
<P>
 Patent Challenge Rebuffed by Appellate Court: Without comment, the U.S. Court 
of Appeals for the Federal Circuit upheld a San Francisco federal judge's 
ruling that NTN Communications of Carlsbad cannot challenge Interactive Network 
Inc.'s patent on an interactive TV game system. Backed by Tele-Communications 
Inc., NBC and other major media firms, Interactive Network markets a system 
that lets viewers play along at home with sports events and game shows.NTN 
alleged that the San Jose firm stole the idea from it, but the decision upheld 
last week ruled that a previous out-of-court settlement barred NTN from raising 
the claim in court. Interactive Network's stock closed at $3 on the Nasdaq 
market, down 18.75 cents; it traded at $12.25 a year ago. 
</P>
