<TEXT>
<P>
 Group Urges FTC Crackdown on 'Misleading' Food Ads: A day after the government 
barred Haagen-Dazs from making low-fat claims about its rich frozen yogurt, a 
consumer organization urged a similar crackdown on other foods.Washington, 
D.C.-based Center for Science in the Public Interest said advertisers routinely 
make misleading claims that foods are more healthful than the data on their 
labels say. Label information is closely regulated by the Food and Drug 
Administration. The Federal Trade Commission has said advertising must adhere 
to many of the same standards as food labels. But CSPI, in a report to be 
delivered to the FTC today, said the agency is not enforcing that policy. 
</P>
