<TEXT>
<P>
 Shell Chemical Agrees to Pay Penalties Related to Explosion: The division of 
Shell Oil Co., the U.S. arm of Royal/Dutch Shell Group, agreed to pay $3.02 
million in penalties to settle charges related to a fatal explosion at an Ohio 
plant, the Labor Department said. Shell Chemical Co. also agreed to make 
significant improvements at its Belpre, Ohio, facility, where an explosion 
killed three workers on May 27, said the department's Occupational Safety & 
Health Administration unit.OSHA said it would issue citations against Shell and 
that the company has agreed not to contest them. "We are very pleased that 
Shell has agreed to resolve this matter as quickly as possible in order to 
ensure maximum protection for its employees," Labor Secretary Robert Reich 
said. Shell said it disputed many of the allegations but that it decided to 
settle the charges to avoid a costly and prolonged legal battle. 
</P>
