<TEXT>
<P>
 Broadway Stores Posts Loss: Broadway Stores Inc. reported a loss of $18.4 
million for the 13-week period ended Oct. 29, compared to a loss of $25.1 
million for the same period a year ago. The Los Angeles-based retailer had 
third quarter sales of $474.9 million, compared to $469.7 million for the 
period a year ago. The company recorded a net loss of $49.3 million for the 39 
weeks ended Oct. 29, compared to a loss of $77.9 million over the same period 
last year. 
</P>
